According to Kasimba Sub-Location assistant chief Pius Odoyo, the matter came to light after a neighbour saw the girl having difficulties in walking.Mr Odoyo said the neighbour asked the minor what was ailing her and it was then that she revealed that she had been defiled.
"Further conversations revealed that the suspect has been defiling the minor," the administrator said.
After the indecent act, the girl would be warned against revealing her ordeal.





Punished
"According to the girl, her uncle threatened her that she would be punished," Mr Odoyo said.
After getting the information, Mr Odoyo rushed to the scene with police from Oyugis police station who arrested the suspect.
The minor was rushed to hospital for medical examination, which revealed that she had been defiled.
The suspect is detained at Oyugis police station and will be charged on Monday.
